The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, April 20, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, April 20, 2004				 																Weather watch				 																																	Finally, some respite in sight. The weatherman says Mondays cloudy sky and light drizzle, that took a scorched city by pleasant surprise, were caused by a four-pronged factor  two low-pressure trough lines and a couple of cyclonic upper-air circulations. And theres something more to smile about. We expect some more rain and possibly a Norwester or two during the next 48 hours, said an official from Alipore Met Office.				 																Screenings				 																																	Andrei Rublyov, directed by Andrei Tarkovsky, will be screened as part of the Cinema in Celebration of Life at Gorky Sadan, at 6 pm.				 																Theatre				 																																	Bengali jatra, Baje Shahnai, Jolchhe Chita, will be staged by Anandamayee Samiti of Bolpur at Bharatiyam, at 6.30 pm.				 																Talk				 																																	Management consultant Gautam Chakravarti will speak on Application of spiritual principles to business in the CMA-Patton Tuesday Talkshoppe at CMA Auditorium on Shakespeare Sarani, at 3.45 pm. 				 																Exhibitions				 																																	An exhibition of illustrations from Indias first graphic novel Corridor, on display at Oxford Bookstore, from 10 am to 9 pm.				 																																	A range of saris, casualwear, linens and accessories on display at Sasha, 27, Mirza Ghalib Street.				 																Art beat				 																																	Rotary Art Vision will be inaugurated at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, at 6.30 pm.
